<!--gc--><div id="abt"><h1 class="item"><span class="fn"> Ghost Rider DVD&#160;Review</span></h1><div id="arate" class="ur"><span class="rating"><span>About.com Rating</span> <span class="value-title threehalf" title="3.5"> <span>3.5 Star Rating</span></span></span></div><div id="urate" class="ur"><span class="rating">Be the first to  <b class="next"><a href="http://reviews.about.com/6843/95f4Jzo00Cqi/submission.htm?bvpage=action.htm&amp;action=AddReview&amp;format=embedded&amp;user=__USERID__&amp;return=http://movies.about.com/od/ghostrider/gr/ghostrider60407.htm&amp;loginparams=__BVLOGINPARAMETERS__&amp;submissionparams=sdn%3Dmovies&amp;campaignid=BV_RATING_SUMMARY_ZERO_REVIEWS&amp;submissionurl=__BVSUBMISSIONURL__">write a review</a></b></span></div><p id="by">By&nbsp;<span class="reviewer"><a href="/bio/Rebecca-Murray-8805.htm" rel="author">Rebecca Murray</a>,&nbsp;About.com Guide</span></p></div>
<div class="tr"><div class="h4">Filed In:</div><ol><li><a href="/od/filmsbygenre" zT="18/1Ys/d2">Films By Genre</a></li><li>&gt; <a href="/od/dramas" zT="18/1Ys/d2">Dramas and Action Films</a></li><li>&gt; <a href="/od/ghostrider" zT="18/1Ys/d2">Ghost Rider</a></li></ol></div>
<div id="abm" class="clear"><div id="abc">

<div id="mimg" class="imgw"><q><img class="photo" src="http://0.tqn.com/d/movies/1/G/b/Y/P/ghostriderdvdreview.jpg" alt="Ghost Rider DVD "></q><p class="cap">Ghost Rider DVD </p><cite>&#169; Sony Pictures Home Entertainment</cite></div>

<div id="sp1" class="sp img"></div><div id="sb1" class="sb"><script type="text/javascript">zSB(3,3)</script><script type="text/javascript">zob();if(zs<1){gEI('sp1').className=gEI('sb1').className='hide';}</script></div>
<div id="articlebody">
<h3 id="grBl">The Bottom Line</h3><div><a href="http://movies.about.com/od/cagenicholas/">Nicolas Cage</a> has always been a huge <i>Ghost Rider</i> fan, and even sports a Ghost Rider tattoo which - interestingly enough - had to be covered over for the film.  Cage's enthusiasm for all things <i>Ghost Rider</i> comes across in the movie, which is a decent comic book movie even non-comic book fans might enjoy.  But if you're investing cash in the DVD, skip the bare bones one-disc version and pick up the two-disc extended version. </div><div id="grLnk1"><a href="http://erclk.about.com/?zi=27/y97"><img src="http://z.about.com/w/bt/bc.gif" alt="Compare Prices" class="cp"></a></div><h3 id="grP">Pros</h3><ul><li>The special effects are terrific</li><li>Nicolas Cage and Eva Mendes have great chemistry</li><li>It's campy without being silly</li></ul><h3 id="grC">Cons</h3><ul><li>The One-Disc DVD doesn't include many bonus features</li></ul><h3 id="grD">Description</h3><ul><li>Commentary by writer/director Mark Steven Johnson and VFX Supervisor Kevin Mack</li><li>Commentary by producer Gary Foster</li><li>'Spirit of Vengeance' - Making Of featurette with behind the scenes footage on the set</li><li>'Spirit of Adventure' - A look at the motorcycle stunts of <i>Ghost Rider</i> and the script</li><li>DVD Release Date: June 12, 2007</li></ul><h3 id="grR">Guide Review - Ghost Rider DVD Review</h3><div>For those not up on the <a href="http://movies.about.com/od/ghostrider/"><i>Ghost Rider</i></a> comics, the story follows a motorcyle stuntman who makes a deal with the devil and becomes a fiery crusader against rogue demons. The film stars Nicolas Cage as Johnny Blaze/Ghost Rider with Eva Mendes portraying his childhood sweetheart Roxanne.<p>

In order to save his father and the girl of his dreams, teenager Johnny Blaze has no alternative but to agree to forge a deal with Mephistopheles (Peter Fonda).  In exchange for saving his dad and Roxanne, an adult Johnny Blaze - now a motorcycle stuntman - transforms into the Ghost Rider. In his fiery form, the Ghost Rider patrols the streets hunting down demons causing trouble.<p>

The action heats up when Mephistopheles reappears in Johnny Blaze's life and offers him a shot at getting back his soul. If Johnny Blaze agrees to hunt down Blackheart (<a href="http://movies.about.com/od/bentleywes/">Wes Bentley</a>), then he'll tear up the deal and Johnny will have his life back...<p>

<b>The Bonus Features</b><p>

The two commentary tracks are about what you'd expect from a comic book-inspired movie's DVD. There's a lot of talk on how scenes were staged and a lot of praising the cast - in particular Nicolas Cage. The two Making Of featurettes on the one-disc DVD version are lengthy, informative and entertaining. <p>  



